   The Energy Department says it has given final
approval to an agreement with Texaco Corp. calling for $1.25
billion in payments to the government over 5{ years to settle
accusations of overcharging for price-controlled crude oil.
   The settlement, formally announced Monday but first detailed in
February, is the second largest in the government's long campaign
to recover overcharges in the years from 1973 to 1981, when crude
