<HEAD>Marcos to Receive Bullet-Proof Mercedes as Gift</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Move over, James Bond.
   Ferdinand Marcos is now the owner of an armor-plated,
bullet-proof automobile, the rival of any car used by Agent 007.
   The deposed Philippines leader, according to an aide, will
receive the customized 1985 Mercedes SEL today as an early birthday
present.
   Marcos spokesman Gemmo Trinidad said supporters on the mainland
believed the car would be a useful birthday present, considering
Marcos' repeated claims that he is stalked by assassins.
   The car, Trinidad said, was shipped here by air freight Monday.
   Honolulu television station KGMB reported Monday that the dark
blue, four-door Mercedes is equipped with features right out of a
spy novel _ including blinding rear lights.
   The car, the station reported, is worth around $150,000 and cost
about $17,000 to ship from the mainland to Hawaii.
   Marcos celebrates his 71st birthday next month.
