<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--DrugSentence     08-30 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Drug Sentence,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Federal Judge Sentences Drug Smuggler to Life in Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A federal judge ordered a convicted drug
smuggler ``removed from society'' and sentenced him to life in
prison without parole for his role in importing 150 tons of
Colombian marijuana.
   Robert Castoro, 39, ``introduced more harm and evil into this
society than a murderer,'' U.S. District Judge Patricia Fawsett
said Monday in imposing the harshest penalty ever handed down in
federal court in Orlando.
   The judge also gave Castoro an additional 65 years in prison on
drug and tax convictions and fined him $200,000.
   Castoro was convicted in July on a charge of conducting a
continuing criminal enterprise and nine other drug possession and
tax-evasion counts.
   Federal drug agents and other witnesses testified he was one of
two major figures controlling a ring that unloaded drug-laden
freighters in the Bahamas and smuggled the marijuana on speedboats
into South Florida from 1977 to 1984.
</TEXT>
