<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five U.S. warships, including the
aircraft carrier John F. Kennedy, arrived Tuesday for a goodwill
visit that Egyptian military sources said would last 10 days.
   The task force includes the missile cruiser Belknap, flagship of
the 6th Fleet commander, Vice Adm. J.D. Williams; the
nuclear-powered missile cruiser Bainbridge; the destroyer John
Rodgers; and the frigate McInerney.
