Mediterranean fleet, went ashore to pay courtesy calls on Maj. Gen.
Sherif Sadek, commander of the navy; Maj. Gen. Ibrahim Atwa, army
commander of the northern zone; and Alexandria Gov. Sayed Gawsaky.
   The United States has been Egypt's main arms supplier and
economic aid donor since 1979.
