<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Washington Poll,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Washingtonians Split Over Presidential Candidates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELLEVUE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bush and Michael Dukakis are
running an even presidential race in Washington state, according to
a recent statewide poll conducted by KIRO-TV and the
Journal-American of Bellevue.
   If the election were held today, 41.3 percent said they would
vote for Democrat Dukakis while 40.8 percent said they would pick
Bush, the Republican candidate.
   The telephone poll, conducted by Consumer Opinion Services of
Seattle, sampled 600 people who identified themselves as registered
voters.
   The poll was taken over the weekend and had a 4 percent margin
of error.
</TEXT>
