<HEAD>Body Was Beneath Bed Several Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OCEANSIDE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The body of a woman apparently beaten to
death was under a motel bed for several days while customers used
the room, police said Tuesday.
   On Sunday, a guest refused to use the room because of a smell.
The body was discovered by a maintenance man on Monday.
   Nassau County police Detective Sgt. John Nolan said the woman
apparently was under the bed in Room 33 of the Oceanside Motel for
several days.
   A toxicology report due in a couple of weeks would determine how
long the woman had been dead, he said.
   The motel's assistant manager, Gary Robinson, said he checked
the room Sunday _ but did not look in the enclosed space beneath
the platform-type bed _ after a Saturday night customer complained
of a smell. He said he didn't find anything but left the door open
to air out the room.
   Police said they had not identified the dead woman.
</TEXT>
