<1ST_LINE>u a AM-People-Springsteen     08-30 0321</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Springsteen,0332</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>The Boss' Wife Files for Divorce</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD De ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Singer-songwriter Bruce Springteen's actress
wife, Julianne Phillips, filed a petition for divorce Tuesday
against the rock superstar, claiming ``irreconcilable differences''
with ``The Boss.''
   The one-page petition filed in Los Angeles Superior Court seeks
unspecified spousal support and says property rights will be
determined later, said attorney Arlene Colman-Schwimmer,
representing Miss Phillips, 28.
   The Springsteens, who were married on May 13, 1985 in Miss
Phillips' hometown of Lake Oswego, Ore., maintain a home in the Los
Angeles area, she said.
   ``Starting the divorce is simple. It's the complications that
arise later that are the problems,'' Ms. Colman-Schwimmer said.
   A spokesman for the singer could not be reached immediately for
comment, and his attorney Barry Slott did not immediately respond
to a message.
   Springsteen, called called ``The Boss'' by his fans, is known
for such rock hits as ``Born To Run,'' ``Thunder Road,'' ``Because
The Night,'' ``Rosalita,'' and ``Tunnel of Love,'' which he
dedicated to Miss Phillips.
   They first met backstage at the Los Angeles Sports Arena during
a concert by Springsteen and his E Street band in October 1984.
   He was riding the crest of his ``Born In The U.S.A'' tour and
album, and she was an aspiring actress and model earning up to
$2,000 a day.
   Rumors began floating late this spring that the couple had
separated. The petition filed Tuesday did not mention a specific
date.
   They have no children, and a spokeswoman for Springsteen has
previously denied reports he and Miss Phillips separated over the
issue of starting a family.
   During this summer's tour to promote his latest ``Tunnel of
Love'' album, Springsteen, 38, has been linked romantically in the
tabloid newspapers with red-haired E Street Band backup singer
Patti Scialfa, 36, who also was on the 1984 tour.
   Springsteen and Miss Scialfa are both natives of New Jersey.
</TEXT>
