   Commercial Credit Group Inc. has agreed
to acquire Primerica Corp. in a cash-and-stock deal valued at $1.65
billion that could create a major force in the financial services
industry.
   Under terms of an agreement approved by both companies' boards,
shareholders would receive one share of Commercial Credit common
stock plus $7 in cash for each share of Primerica.
   The combined companies expect to operate under the Primerica
name, the chairmen of both companies said Monday.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New home sales suffered their steepest drop in
seven months during July, the government says, and economists
predict further softening as rising mortgage interest rates push up
the cost of buying a home.
   Sales of new single-family homes fell 4.7 percent to a
seasonally-adjusted annual rate of 686,000 units last month,
according to a joint report Monday of the departments of Commerce
and Housing and Urban Development.
</TEXT>
