<TEXT>
   The Energy Department has approved an
agreement with Texaco Corp. calling for $1.25 billion in payments
to the government over 5{ years to settle accusations of
overcharging for price-controlled crude oil.
   The settlement approved Monday is the second largest in the
government's long campaign to recover overcharges in the years from
1973 to 1981, when crude oil was subject to price controls.
   Only the $2.1 billion paid by Exxon Corp. was larger. With the
Texaco payment, the government will have recovered more than $7
billion.
