   One of every four U.S. workers is a college
graduate, compared with just one in five 10 years ago, the Labor
Department says.
   An additional 20 percent, up from 16 percent a decade ago, have
completed one to three years of college, according to the new data
released Monday by the Bureau of Labor Statistics.
</TEXT>
