<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pressured by dissatisfied
shareholders, American Medical International Inc. called a meeting
today to oust its chairman and chief executive officer, Walter L.
Weisman.
   Royce Diener, a director and former chief executive officer, was
to be named as an interim replacement, the company said Monday.
   A committee of non-management directors called for Weisman's
resignation after the company's four largest stockholders objected
to an earlier recommendation that Weisman keep his job, the company
said.
   The hospital company has been selling underperforming hospitals
and cutting staff in an attempt to boost its earnings.
